{"componentChunkName":"component---src-templates-docs-js","path":"/docs/parent-theme.html","result":{"data":{"markdownRemark":{"html":"<p>ScandiPWA v3 (currently in beta) supports implementing parent themes, which allow extending some custom theme that extends vendor theme. This functionality is convenient if one likes to use <em>his own theme</em> that extends <code class=\"gatsby-code-text\">scandipwa/source</code> as the project’s base instead of <code class=\"gatsby-code-text\">scandipwa/source</code> itself.</p>\n<h2 id=\"a-step-by-step-algorithm-of-implementing-a-parent-theme\"><a href=\"#a-step-by-step-algorithm-of-implementing-a-parent-theme\" aria-hidden class=\"anchor\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" height=\"16\" version=\"1.1\" viewBox=\"0 0 16 16\" width=\"16\"><path fill-rule=\"evenodd\" d=\"M4 9h1v1H4c-1.5 0-3-1.69-3-3.5S2.55 3 4 3h4c1.45 0 3 1.69 3 3.5 0 1.41-.91 2.72-2 3.25V8.59c.58-.45 1-1.27 1-2.09C10 5.22 8.98 4 8 4H4c-.98 0-2 1.22-2 2.5S3 9 4 9zm9-3h-1v1h1c1 0 2 1.22 2 2.5S13.98 12 13 12H9c-.98 0-2-1.22-2-2.5 0-.83.42-1.64 1-2.09V6.25c-1.09.53-2 1.84-2 3.25C6 11.31 7.55 13 9 13h4c1.45 0 3-1.69 3-3.5S14.5 6 13 6z\"></path></svg></a>A step-by-step algorithm of implementing a parent theme</h2>\n<ol>\n<li>Implement your custom theme, you can refer to <a href=\"./extension.html\">this guide</a>.</li>\n<li>Create a parent theme directory: <code class=\"gatsby-code-text\">app/design/frontend/&lt;vendor&gt;/&lt;themename&gt;</code> or use the default <code class=\"gatsby-code-text\">app/design/frontend/Scandiweb/pwa_parent</code>.</li>\n<li>Reference that directory in the <code class=\"gatsby-code-text\">scandipwa.json</code> file in the root of your project, field <code class=\"gatsby-code-text\">parentRoot</code>. The path should be relative to <code class=\"gatsby-code-text\">app/design/frontend</code> directory.</li>\n</ol>\n<div\n              class=\"gatsby-code-button-container\"\n              data-toaster-id=\"69751839091649724000\"\n              data-toaster-class=\"gatsby-code-button-toaster customToasterClass\"\n              data-toaster-text-class=\"gatsby-code-button-toaster-text customToasterTextClass\"\n              data-toaster-text=\"Copied\"\n              data-toaster-duration=\"3500\"\n              onClick=\"copyToClipboard(`{\n    &quot;parentRoot&quot;: &quot;<vendor>/<themename>&quot;\n}`, `69751839091649724000`)\"\n            >\n              <div\n                class=\"gatsby-code-button customButtonClass\"\n                data-tooltip=\"\"\n              >\n                Copy<svg class=\"gatsby-code-button-icon\" xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/2000/svg\" width=\"24\" height=\"24\" viewBox=\"0 0 24 24\"><path fill=\"none\" d=\"M0 0h24v24H0V0z\"/><path d=\"M16 1H2v16h2V3h12V1zm-1 4l6 6v12H6V5h9zm-1 7h5.5L14 6.5V12z\"/></svg>\n              </div>\n            </div>\n<div class=\"gatsby-highlight\" data-language=\"jsx\"><pre class=\"gatsby-code-jsx\"><code class=\"gatsby-code-jsx\"><span class=\"token punctuation\">{</span>\n    <span class=\"token string\">\"parentRoot\"</span><span class=\"token operator\">:</span> <span class=\"token string\">\"&lt;vendor>/&lt;themename>\"</span>\n<span class=\"token punctuation\">}</span></code></pre></div>\n<ol start=\"4\">\n<li>Move your custom theme’s contents there (<code class=\"gatsby-code-text\">mv -r pwa/* pwa_parent/*</code>) and then erase the <code class=\"gatsby-code-text\">pwa</code> directory.</li>\n<li>Restart the project in order to re-create the <code class=\"gatsby-code-text\">pwa</code> folder from scratch.</li>\n<li>If in your custom theme you had anything changed in the files that now populate the <code class=\"gatsby-code-text\">pwa</code> directory, migrate the changes back.</li>\n<li>Start implementing a theme on top of your theme! Work in the <code class=\"gatsby-code-text\">pwa</code> directory just as you are used to.</li>\n<li>\n<p>Implement desired logic!</p>\n<ul>\n<li>Extending files. First you need to import something you want to extend. To import files from parent theme use the alias <code class=\"gatsby-code-text\">Parent&lt;...&gt;</code>, to import from source theme use the alias <code class=\"gatsby-code-text\">Source&lt;...&gt;</code>. E.g. to import <code class=\"gatsby-code-text\">AddToCart</code> component (and extend it) use the following:</li>\n</ul>\n</li>\n</ol>\n<div\n              class=\"gatsby-code-button-container\"\n              data-toaster-id=\"8353008824002295000\"\n              data-toaster-class=\"gatsby-code-button-toaster customToasterClass\"\n              data-toaster-text-class=\"gatsby-code-button-toaster-text customToasterTextClass\"\n              data-toaster-text=\"Copied\"\n              data-toaster-duration=\"3500\"\n              onClick=\"copyToClipboard(`    // To extend source component\n    import SourceAddToCart from 'SourceComponent/AddToCart';\n    class AddToCart extends SourceAddToCart { ... }\n\n    // Or to extend parent theme's component\n    import ParentAddToCart from 'ParentComponent/AddToCart';\n    class AddToCart extends ParentAddToCart { ... }`, `8353008824002295000`)\"\n            >\n              <div\n                class=\"gatsby-code-button customButtonClass\"\n                data-tooltip=\"\"\n              >\n                Copy<svg class=\"gatsby-code-button-icon\" xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/2000/svg\" width=\"24\" height=\"24\" viewBox=\"0 0 24 24\"><path fill=\"none\" d=\"M0 0h24v24H0V0z\"/><path d=\"M16 1H2v16h2V3h12V1zm-1 4l6 6v12H6V5h9zm-1 7h5.5L14 6.5V12z\"/></svg>\n              </div>\n            </div>\n<div class=\"gatsby-highlight\" data-language=\"jsx\"><pre class=\"gatsby-code-jsx\"><code class=\"gatsby-code-jsx\">    <span class=\"token comment\">// To extend source component</span>\n    <span class=\"token keyword\">import</span> SourceAddToCart <span class=\"token keyword\">from</span> <span class=\"token string\">'SourceComponent/AddToCart'</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">;</span>\n    <span class=\"token keyword\">class</span> <span class=\"token class-name\">AddToCart</span> <span class=\"token keyword\">extends</span> <span class=\"token class-name\">SourceAddToCart</span> <span class=\"token punctuation\">{</span> <span class=\"token operator\">...</span> <span class=\"token punctuation\">}</span>\n\n    <span class=\"token comment\">// Or to extend parent theme's component</span>\n    <span class=\"token keyword\">import</span> ParentAddToCart <span class=\"token keyword\">from</span> <span class=\"token string\">'ParentComponent/AddToCart'</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">;</span>\n    <span class=\"token keyword\">class</span> <span class=\"token class-name\">AddToCart</span> <span class=\"token keyword\">extends</span> <span class=\"token class-name\">ParentAddToCart</span> <span class=\"token punctuation\">{</span> <span class=\"token operator\">...</span> <span class=\"token punctuation\">}</span></code></pre></div>\n<ul>\n<li>Using components. To import component and use it somewhere in your application (not to extend it) use the regular <code class=\"gatsby-code-text\">Component/&lt;ComponentName&gt;</code> alias. When resolving a file, Fallback plugin is going to look in the following directories subsequently:</li>\n<li>Custom theme (<code class=\"gatsby-code-text\">app/design/frontend/.../pwa</code>)</li>\n<li>Parent theme (<code class=\"gatsby-code-text\">parentRoot</code> in scandipwa.json)</li>\n<li>Vendor theme (<code class=\"gatsby-code-text\">src/scandipwa/source</code>)</li>\n</ul>","frontmatter":{"title":"Implementing a parent theme"},"fields":{"path":"content/docs/parent-theme.md","slug":"/docs/parent-theme.html"}}},"pageContext":{"slug":"/docs/parent-theme.html"}},"staticQueryHashes":[]}